rComments: Professor Molnar clearly knows his stuff when it comes to ecology. He is not a nice prof at all and he made me overwhelmed for the entire semester and his class is so boring and all so you need to read textbook for his tests. I do not recommend him take this course with another prof if you can.

Very boring lecturer and an even more boring course. He speaks so fast and doesn't teach the material. His short answers on the exams were marked crazy hard it was impossible to do well. Doesn't have the students best interest at heart.
As far as ecology goes, he seems to be one of the better profs. Read the textbook but focus on his slides.

The problem he fails to realize is 99% of students who took this course were forced to. He already loses out on this so combining with the super boring teaching style, 100% of students will settle for something else but ecology, period. Very knowledgable professor. Very intelligent in the mathematics. A bit awkward at times but very approachable. He takes his time to explain things if you ask him, and is a really nice guy and willing to help. Pace of his slides is good. Assignments are fair. Love this prof.

hated how the biob50 midterm exam was a day after the biob10 midterm exam. it was so hard to study for both. get ready to memorize a ton of equations. he literally covers most of the material in the textbook. he basically just reads off the lecture slides and tries to get through them but that does not end up happening. oh its also not weboptioned.
